        <p><strong>PerlScript</strong> was initially solely an {'ActiveX'|link_urls:'i'} Scripting Engine produced by the company ActiveState for use with Microsoft's Internet Information Services ({'IIS'|link_urls:'w'}) that allows for programmers to use Perl-based code in addition to, or in place of, {'VBScript'|link_urls:'/l'} or {'JScript'|link_urls:'/l'} in the context of web servers running the {'ASP'|link_urls:'/l'} protocol.</p>
        <p>Subsequently <strong>Apache::ASP</strong> was created for the {'Apache'|link_urls:'w'} web server, which allows for coding with only {'Perl'|link_urls:'/l'}, but neither VBScript nor JScript.</p>
